                                                                                                                                   Forest rights

              
	New Delhi, Jan. 1 (PTI): The Centre today issued a notification for implementing the provisions of the Scheduled Tribes Forest Rights Act that gives forest dwellers exclusive rights over its resources.
    
	Major rights recognised under the act include those to cultivate forest land subject to a ceiling of four hectares, to collect, use and dispose of minor forest products, and traditional and customary rights. 
                                                                                
